ENTRY       EC 4.2.3.13                 Enzyme
NAME        (+)-delta-cadinene synthase
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Acting on phosphates
SYSNAME     (2E,6E)-farnesyl-diphosphate diphosphate-lyase (cyclizing, (+)-delta-cadinene-forming)
REACTION    (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate = (+)-delta-cadinene + diphosphate [RN:R02311]
ALL_REAC    R02311
SUBSTRATE   (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate [CPD:C00448]
PRODUCT     (+)-delta-cadinene [CPD:C06394];
            diphosphate [CPD:C00013]
COMMENT     The sesquiterpenoid (+)-delta-cadinene is an intermediate in phytoalexin biosynthesis. Mg2+ is required for activity.
